HELP: I’m not sure where else to get help but......




I ordered a phone case for my sister Dec 5th so it would get her as her Christmas present from the Try Guys merch store. We watch their videos together when I’m home from college and we got close again after watching them. It’s been almost two full months and nothing. I’ve sent 10 emails to the third company they use, sent tweets and nothing. The tracking number doesn’t work. The emails don’t work. The tweets don’t work. I just want my money back at this point, I can’t even enjoy watching the videos knowing I spent $30 on a case that never arrived and my sister didn’t get her present. idk what else to do. Has anyone else experienced difficulties with their store of this kind? There’s no phone number to get in contact and I don’t know what else to do...

snippet.textDisplay: This may be my first comment on a video ever. I absolutely LOVE the Try Guys, food videos, sushi, and watching people eat, and at first I was excited to watch this new video! However, with the extreme overfishing of high-grade sushi fishes such as tuna and salmon species, I quickly began to find this video really depressing. Unsustainable delicacies like this should be savored and enjoyed, not stuffed down like a hot dog (although treating any meat like a challenge to eat in massive quantities or super quickly rather than something you are lucky to enjoy in limited amounts -- even something as low-grade as a hot dog -- is pretty awful in my opinion). I'm honestly surprised that someone as environmentally conscious as Zach would be cool with this video. I don't intend criticize or offend the Try Guys! I love you! Just felt the urge to say something.
